<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="484" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1767,1902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1767,1794]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(from 
<bibRefCitation author="Fachin, D. A. &amp; Santos, C. M. D. &amp; Amorim, D. S." box="[346,557,1767,1794]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484" pagination="557 - 574" refId="ref6130" refString="Fachin, D. A., Santos, C. M. D. &amp; Amorim, D. S. (2018) First two species of Austroleptis Hardy (Diptera: Brachycera: Austroleptidae) from Brazil. Zootaxa, 4369 (4), 557 - 574. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4369.4.6" type="journal article" year="2018">
Fachin 
<emphasis box="[431,488,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Antenna with 3–5 flagellomeres, basal flagellomere enlarged, laterally compressed, distal flagellomeres not narrow and elongated. Clypeus subtriangular, recessed beneath head. M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1333,1341,1821,1835]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">3</subScript>
missing or reduced to a small stump between M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[586,594,1857,1871]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">2</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[671,679,1857,1871]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">4</subScript>
emerging from the discal cell. Male gonocoxal apodeme absent. Female segments 6–8 much narrower than preceding abdominal segments, tergite 8 divided, cercus one-segmented.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
